      "summary": "Founded in <cite id=\"1\">1969</cite>, the Union of Concerned Scientists (UCS) is a premier science-based advocacy organization dedicated to solving the planet's most pressing environmental and safety problems. The organization reported <cite id=\"2\">$41,698,808 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year, leveraging these funds to drive technical analysis and policy innovation. UCS operates with high financial efficiency, maintaining an <cite id=\"3\">87.8% program expense ratio</cite>, which ensures that the vast majority of donor contributions directly support its research and advocacy initiatives. Their work spans critical areas including <cite id=\"4\">climate and energy, clean transportation, and global security</cite>. The organization is highly regarded for its transparency and accountability, holding a <cite id=\"5\">99.5/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite> and a <cite id=\"6\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>. Beyond its internal research, UCS acts as a strategic funder, distributing <cite id=\"7\">$637,100 in domestic grants</cite> to partner organizations to amplify its impact on the transition to a low-carbon power system.",
